==历史==
印度的学校教育已经有很长的历史。<!-- [[Gurukul|Gurukul]] system of education is one of the oldest on earth but before that the guru shishya system was extant, in which students were taught orally and the data would be passed from one generation to the next. Gurukuls were traditional Hindu residential schools of learning; typically the teacher's house or a monastery. Education was free, but students from well-to-do families payed Gurudakshina, a voluntary contribution after the completion of their studies. At the Gurukuls, the teacher imparted knowledge of 宗教、Scriptures, [[哲学|哲学]]、[[文学|文学]], Warfare, Statecraft, [[Ayurveda|Medicine]] Astrology and History (the Sanskrit word "[[Itihaas|Itihaas]]" means History). The first millennium and the few centuries preceding it saw the flourishing of higher education at [[Nalanda|Nalanda]], [[Takshashila_University|Takshashila University]], [[Ujjain|Ujjain]], & [[Vikramshila|Vikramshila]] Universities.艺术，建筑，绘画，逻辑，语法，哲学，天文，文学，[[佛教|佛教]], [[印度教|印度教]], [[Arthashastra|Arthashastra]] (Economics & Politics), Law, and Medicine were among the subjects taught and each university specialized in a particular field of study. Takshila specialized in the study of medicine, while Ujjain laid emphasis on astronomy. Nalanda, being the biggest centre, handled all branches of knowledge, and housed up to 10,000 students at its peak. -->

===17世纪以前===

印度人没有记录历史的传统, 所以即便是学者对印度古代的教育情况也了解不多, 在[[回教|回教]]王朝时代, [[贵族|贵族]]学习的内容有[[印地文|印地文]], [[数学|数学]], [[科学|科学]],[[波斯文|波斯文]]等
<!-- The first millennium and the few centuries preceding it saw the flourishing of higher education at [[Nalanda|Nalanda]], [[Takshila|Takshila]], [[Ujjain|Ujjain]], & [[Vikramshila|Vikramshila]] Universities.艺术，建筑，绘画，逻辑，语法，哲学，天文，文学，[[佛教|佛教]], [[印度教|印度教]], [[Arthashastra|Arthashastra]] (Economics & Politics), Law, and Medicine were among the subjects taught and each university specialized in a particular field of study. Takshila specialized in the study of medicine, while Ujjain laid emphasis on astronomy. Nalanda, being the biggest centre, handled all branches of knowledge, and housed up to 10,000 students at its peak. -->

===英国统治时期===
[[File:Thomas_Babington_Macaulay,_1st_Baron_Macaulay_-_Project_Gutenberg_eText_13103.jpg|thumb]]
[http://www.infinityfoundation.com/mandala/t_es/t_es_goyal_education.htm 英国人的文献纪录] {{Wayback|url=http://www.infinityfoundation.com/mandala/t_es/t_es_goyal_education.htm |date=20200815054155 }}表明，在18世纪的印度大部分地区，教育相当普及，每一个寺庙，清真寺或乡村都有一所学校。教授的课程包括阅读、写作、算术，神学，法律，天文，形而上学，伦理学，医学与宗教。学校的学生来自社会各阶层。

目前的教育体制具有西方的风格和内容，于19世纪根据[[托马斯·巴宾顿·麦考利，第一代麦考利男爵|麦考利]]的建议，由英国人引进并资助，传统的教育不被英国政府承认，从此衰落。[[甘地|甘地]]说传统的教育体系如同一棵美丽的树，在英国统治期间被摧毁。  

英国人在印度建立了许多大学，例如[[圣沙勿略学院|圣沙勿略学院]]（St. Xaviers College），[[锡德纳姆学院|锡德纳姆学院]]（Sydenham College），[[威尔逊学院|威尔逊学院]]（Wilson College）和[[埃尔芬斯学院|埃尔芬斯学院]]（Elphinstone College）。 

[[喀拉拉邦|喀拉拉邦]]的第一个医学院开始于[[卡利卡特|卡利卡特]]，[[二战|二战]]期间的1942至43年。由于缺少服务军事的医生 ，英国政府决定在马拉巴尔开设[[马德拉斯医学院|马德拉斯医学院]]的分校。战争结束后，卡利卡特的医学院关闭，学生在马德拉斯医学院继续学业。

独立以后，教育成为[[国家|国家]]的责任。

===教育统筹委员会===
由博士[[D.S.科塔里|D.S.科塔里]]，当时的大学资助委员会主席，于 1964 年 10 月 2 日开始其任务。它由十六名成员组成，其中十一名是印度人和五名外国专家。此外，委员会还与教育和科学领域的一些国际知名顾问进行了讨论。

==教育开支==
自从第一个五年计划，印度政府在教育方面的开支大大增加。印度政府大幅补贴高等教育。中央政府对基础教育经费的97%用于发放教师工资。

==批评==

现代印度教育经常被批评为基于[[机械学习|机械学习]]（rote learning），重点强调考试的通过率，很少有学校重视学生人格与创造性的发展。<!-- Recently, the country has seen a rise in instances of student suicides due to low marks and failures, especially in metropolitan cities, even though such cases are very rare. 

The presence of a number of education boards (SSC, [[ICSE|ICSE]], [[CBSE|CBSE]], [[IB|IB]]) leads to non-uniformity. ICSE and CBSE boards, being quite tougher than SSC, are favourably considered at the time of admission. A large number of SSC (State board) students therefore complain that their ICSE and CBSE counterparts are given an advantage during college admissions, which are extremely competitive and sought for. Most colleges though account for these differences during admissions. The syllabi prescribed by the various boards are accused of being archaic and some textbooks (mostly ones written for the SSC) contain many errors. -->

<!-- The boards are recently trying to improve quality of education by increasing percentage of practical and project marks. However, critics say even this is memorized by students (or even [[plagiarism|plagiarized]]). This is attributed to pressure from parents who are eager to see high scores more than overall development. -->

<!-- Many people also criticize the [[Reservation_in_India|caste, language and religion-based reservations]] in education system. Many allege that very few of the weaker castes get the benefit of reservations and that forged caste certificates abound. Educational institutions also can seek ''religious minority'' (non-Hindu) or ''linguistic minority'' status. In such institutions, 50% of the seats are reserved for students belonging to a particular [[religion|religion]] or having particular [[mother-tongue|mother-tongue]](s). For example, many colleges run by the [[Jesuits|Jesuits]] and [[Salesians_of_Don_Bosco|Salesians]] have 50% seats reserved for [[Roman_Catholics|Roman Catholics]]. In case of languages, an institution can declare itself linguistic minority only in states in which the language is not official language. For example, an engineering college can declare itself as linguistic-minority ([[Hindi|Hindi]]) institution in the state of [[Maharashtra|Maharashtra]] (where official state language is [[Marathi|Marathi]]), but not in [[Madhya_Pradesh|Madhya Pradesh]] or [[Uttar_Pradesh|Uttar Pradesh]] (where the official state language is [[Hindi|Hindi]]). These reservations are said to be a cause of heartbreak among many. Many students with poor marks manage to get admissions, while  meritorious students are left out. Critics say that such reservations may eventually create rifts in the society. -->

<!-- The general [[political_corruption|corruption]] prevalent in India is also an issue in the Education system. Engineering, medical and other lucrative seats are sometimes sold for high prices and ridden with nepotism and power-play.

[[Student_politics|Student politics]] is also a major issue, as many institutions are run by [[politician|politician]]s.

[[Ragging|Ragging]] used to be a major problem in colleges, but tough rules and regulations have curbed it. Some state governments have made ragging a criminal offence. -->


